<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1915-07-31T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1915-07-31T00:00:00-05:00" n="721" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d721">
                            <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 841.857Ib3/2</note>
                            <head>
                                <hi rend="italic">The Consul at Cork</hi> (<persName corresp="#p_FW1" type="from"><hi rend="italic">Frost</hi></persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss>
                                </hi>
                            </head>
                            <opener>
                                <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram]</seg>
                            </opener>
                            <opener>
                                <dateline rendition="#right">
                                    <placeName>
                                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Queenstown</hi></placeName>, <date ana="#date_undated-inferred-from-document-content-and-sibling-dates" calendar="gregorian" when="1915-07-31"><hi rend="italic">undated</hi></date>.<lb/>[<hi rend="italic">Received
                                        July 31, 1915, 8.20 p. m.</hi>]</dateline>
                            </opener>
                            <p>Burns changes statement. Says submarine fired two shots before
                                    ship<note n="1" xml:id="d721fn1">See the case of the <hi rend="italic">Iberian, ante</hi>, <ref target="#pg_492">p.
                                        492</ref>.</note> sought to stop, then several more before
                                submarine, which was dead astern, appeared to realize ship had
                                stopped.</p>
                            <closer>
                                <signed>
                                    <persName corresp="#p_FW1">
                                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Frost</hi>
                                    </persName>
                                </signed>
                            </closer>
                        </div>
                        </body></text></TEI>